📌 Profile Optimisation
"Act like the world’s best Instagram marketer with 10 years of experience. My Instagram profile is about (insert your niche here). I need help creating a short Instagram bio that stands out. The bio should have 3 short lines:
1. First line: Clearly state what I do and how I can help people (e.g., 'I help X achieve Y'), and make it impactful and memorable.
2. Second line: Highlight my mission and explain how people will benefit from my content.
3. Third line: Include a strong call to action that grabs attention and gets people interested.”

✍🏼 Reel Caption Prompt
“Act as the best copywriter in the world, known for your mastery of storytelling and engaging writing. Write a fun, impactful caption about {insert content pillar, e.g., Sales strategy tip}, using simple and easy-to-understand English for my audience. The title/subject is: {insert the hook title}. The caption is: {insert the reference caption/your previous caption}.”

🎞️ Carousel Post Generator Prompt
“Act as the best copywriter in the world, specializing in crafting storytelling carousel posts. Create a 4-5 slide carousel with specific, actionable examples, focusing on {content pillar} the audience so they’ll want to share it with others. Use simple, conversational English to make it easy to follow. The topic is {insert topic name}. Here's a reference link: {insert the link as a reference}.”

🪝 Generate catchy & unique hooks
“As a content creator in the {insert your business/niche}, my goal is to engage my audience to {insert desired outcome}. Provide 10 irresistible, engaging hooks that’ll captivate my audience & keep them hooked to watch till the end with easy English.”

🍒 Generate viral story ideas
“Act as the world’s best Instagram marketer with 10 years of experience. Your task is to generate 10 viral Instagram Story ideas for my audience. The main objective is to boost engagement and increase views. Create fresh, unique, and out-of-the-box ideas that I can use in (insert niche).”

caption.text:
🔔 Drop 'SECRET' below then I'll send you my FREE IG Growth Tutorials that helped me grow 137k followers.

Here’s my winning formula👇🏻

1️⃣ Focus on Giving First 😇
I focus on giving as much as I can. Create lots of freebies and use ManyChat to share them. When you add your freebie link, you can also add your services and products there—this way, it feels less like selling. (You can include more than one link!)

2️⃣ What My Viral Reels Have in Common:
All my viral reels start with a strong hook using numbers + visuals. Numbers catch people's attention because they help organize info quickly.
⚡️ Some examples: "in 2 minutes," "4 months ago," "10 ways to..." Numbers work because we want fast results. Keep it simple and get to the point!

3️⃣ Visuals Are Important
My favorite filming style = time-lapse & transitions. Put 90% of your effort into making the first 3 seconds stand out.

⚡️ Use quick cuts (0.4 to 0.6 seconds) to make your reel more fun, and add text that matches the beat of the music.

⚡️ Before you film, do these:
☑ Clean your camera lens
☑ Export to 1080*1920 / 30fps
☑ Set up high-quality uploads on Instagram (check the pinned comment for tips)
☑ Film in 4K or 1080 / 30fps
☑ Turn off HDR settings

4️⃣ Do Your Research!
Check out other creators' best content. Look at how they film, their text hooks, audio choices, and captions. Learn from what works for them!

5️⃣ How to Attract People to Your Services:
➡️ Offer Value First (Like I mentioned No.1)

➡️ Make Your Offers Simple
Use ManyChat AI to automate and make it easy for people to understand what you offer. Create a clear and simple path from discovering your content to purchasing your services. For example:
↳ Instead of using “Link in bio” X use this statement “Comment “IG” to get your FREE guide”

🫶 Share this with someone who needs it!

📌 If you found me today, it’s a sign you’re ready to say goodbye to those endless hours spent on creating content. 🚫

Here are my proven tips below: 

[→] Tip #1: Plan Your Month
Set aside one day each month to brainstorm ideas. For instance, create weekly themes—like “Motivation Monday” or “Tip Tuesday.” This gives you direction and takes the guesswork out of posting!

[→] Tip #2: Batch your work 
if you’re writing a caption, try to write four posts in a few hours. It helps you stay in the creative mood and saves you time!

[→] Tip #2: Repurpose Like a Pro
Don’t be afraid of repurposing your old content (usually, 70-90 days ago)
reuse and recycle them to reach your audience in different ways!

[→] Tip #4: Schedule and Relax
Reels - Post manually (my own preference)
Carousel posts & IG Stories - I use Meta Business Suite (FREE)
Set it up and let it run! This frees you up to engage with your audience instead of scrambling to post last minute.

[→] Tip #5: The POWER of cross post
The new Pinterest feature lets you connect your Instagram link. This way, whenever you post something on Instagram, it will automatically post on Pinterest too, so you don’t have to do it twice.
⭐️ HOW? Settings > Claimed accounts > Click ‘Claim’ on IG > Done!
I also post content on TikTok after posting IG content so don’t forget to download your reel from draft and re-post on your secondary social media platform!

✨Reel templates that actually convert your viewer into followers

Want to Stay Consistent with Social Media? Let me tell you how I do it. 

To be honest, I’m a very forgetful person. If I don’t organize my content, my mind gets messy, and it makes me feel nervous. Am I the only one? That’s why I prefer a simple weekly planner to stay ahead of what I need to do.

🤳 Of course, I plan to create topics for my monthly content, but there’s no need to stress about having everything perfect for the whole month.

Let’s focus on the most recent content and stay present 😉

Keeping up with social media can be tough, but planning ahead makes it easier. 🗓️

I use this creative weekly planner to organize everything. It’s simple and lets me manually add all the info I need to stay on track.

Here’s why it works: 
✅ Save Time: Planning posts in advance frees up your schedule. 
✅ Stay Consistent: Regular posting builds trust with your audience. 
✅ Create Better Content: Thoughtful planning leads to higher-quality posts. 
✅ Track Progress: See what’s working and adjust as needed.

✅ Reason for Change:
➪ Instagram wants creators to focus on how many people see their content (reach), not just follower counts.
➪ Users now see more content recommended by Instagram’s AI, rather than only what they follow.
➪ More than 50% of posts you see are from accounts Instagram thinks you might like, not just from accounts you follow.

✅ Less Focus on Following: People are caring less about who they follow and more about what the algorithm shows them.

✅ More Sharing in DMs: Instead of just liking posts, users are sharing content more through direct messages.

💫 What Creators Should Do:
➪ Focus on increasing the number of views and how many people your content reaches.
➪ Create content that Instagram’s algorithm is likely to recommend to more people.
➪ Building a big following is getting harder, so it’s more important to look at how your content performs in views and shares.

✅ Adjust your strategies to focus on these new metrics, understanding that follower counts are now less important.

A lot of people have been asking me what fonts I use, especially for carousel posts.

💭 Drop “VIS” below then I’ll send you my FREE Branding Kit and how you can build a memorable personal brand.

✨ Subheadline: Dreaming outloud sans
